KMmeans Clustering Algorithm¶

The simplest algorithm used for the clustering ,¶

Intuition¶

The points are nearer to the center of their clusters¶

So let's now see how this works¶

1) Let's assume that the points plottted and mew be their centres¶

let a be assignments and u (mew ) be the centres or labels that we are yet to determine¶

So the equation that needs to be minimise is given above ,¶

here i = (1 to n) is number of points or assignments¶

here j = (1 to K) is the number of labels or centres¶

How can we minimise this equation ?¶

we minimise the equation by following the below steps¶

a) Choose optimal assignments (a) for a fixed centre (u) mew¶

b) Choose optimal center (u) for fixed assignments (a)¶

Repeat the steps until convergence¶

how to achieve ? ?¶

a) Choose optimal assignments (a) for a fixed centre (u) mew¶

step a is easily achieved by assigning the points to their nearest centres , note that now the centres were randomnly chosen in this step¶

how to achieve below ??¶

b) Choose optimal center (u) for fixed assignments (a)¶

1) so we now write the eucledian distance in the equation L as a dot product of two matrices¶

2 ) In order to minimise L let's take differential at particular center (j) , and since we now take only one jth center , the resulting equation has only one summation on i = (1...n)¶

3) replacing with vector multiplication we get -2x+2u¶

4) thus we can get an equation for u now which depends assignments by equating L to zero¶

5) differentiating agan with respect to kth element of centre j we get the last equation above here e is the identity matrix¶

6) substituiting with the number of elements (n) to the equation we finally get that center (u) lies on the mean of all the assignments to j¶

So now we can simply follow below steps for kmeans¶
